com.camerontec.catalys.util.messaging

Class MessageBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.messaging.MessageBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMessage, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConnectionStatusMessage, ExceptionMessage, ResetMessage

    public class MessageBase
extends Object
implements IMessage, Serializable
    Convenient base class for IMessage objects.

    It supports history as a transient attribute - ie the history will be lost during serialization.

      • getHistory

        public List<IMessageProcessor> getHistory()
        Description copied from interface: IMessage
        A message may carry some history with it in the form of a list of objects. This history may, for example, contain information as to where a message has been routed. Each object that processes the message could add an entry to the history.

        If a message does not support history it can return null on this call.

        Specified by:
        getHistory in interface IMessage
        Returns:
        The history list or null if history not supported.

      • getRoutingHint

        public Object getRoutingHint()
        Description copied from interface: IMessage
        Returns hint on where the message is destined to be sent.

        May be null.

        This may be useful to distinguish the direction of messages. For example, in a point to point connection between a stock broker and a stock market, this hint may return one of two possible values which indicate whether the message is heading to the market or to the broker. This sort of distinction would be useful in components that process messages in both directions. The component would receive the message and then may process it differently depending on the direction the message is heading.

        Specified by:
        getRoutingHint in interface IMessage
        Returns:
        An object indicating the ultimate destination of the message. May be null.

      • setHistory

        public void setHistory(List<IMessageProcessor> history)
        Description copied from interface: IMessage
        This can be used to completely reset a message's history.

        Any existing history is lost.

        This is not the usual way to update history (you would normally just get the history list and add to it). It is useful for copying history from one message to another.

        Specified by:
        setHistory in interface IMessage
        Parameters:
        history - The history which should be associated with the message.
